    "biography": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Warden-Sergeant Eirik Greyhand</strong> commands the Chainwarden Toll at Greypass&mdash;a fortified checkpoint in the Midgard's Shield foothills. He is not corrupt, just exhausted. The toll is underfunded, understaffed, and overwhelmed by refugees.</p><p>Eirik wants order. He wants the fiction that the system works. He desperately needs supplies&mdash;fuel and rations are worth more than coin. He has a family in Hrafnborg and hasn't heard from them in a month; any news is worth something to him.</p>",
      "director": "<p>Eirik is the Beat 4 negotiation encounter at the Greypass Toll. He is not an antagonist&mdash;he's a cog in a machine that's breaking down.</p><p><strong>Negotiation approaches:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Present forged papers (Presence):</strong> Tier 2+: satisfied. Tier 1: notices seal is wrong&mdash;+1 Interest (suspicious but curious).</li><li><strong>Offer rations or fuel:</strong> Tier 2+: earns 2 Interest immediately, waves them through, offers road intelligence.</li><li><strong>Share news of Hrafnborg (Presence):</strong> Tier 2+: visible relief, +1 Interest.</li><li><strong>Bluff military connection (Presence):</strong> Tier 3 only: buys it. Tier 1&ndash;2: he knows every Warden&mdash;&minus;1 Patience.</li><li><strong>Threaten or intimidate:</strong> Catastrophic. 8 wardens and fortified position. &minus;2 Patience.</li><li><strong>Present Bryn's toll-token:</strong> One party member passes free. Asks after Bryn.</li></ul><p>In Beat 8, the toll-post is dark on the return journey. Eirik has evacuated south. A note on the door reads: 'Recalled to Hrafnborg. Orders of the King.'&mdash;illustrating the system collapsing inward.</p>",
      "languages": []
    },
